Names: Numair Hasan, Darren Chuang
NetIDs: mnh83, dlc286

Testing Plan:
- Two identical files: expect JSD of 0.00000
- Two completely different files: expect JSD of 1.00000
- "hi there hi there" vs "hi hi out there": expect JSD of 0.39451
- Directory traversal: confirm .txt files in subdirectories are found.
- Explicit non-.txt file given as argument: confirm it is included
- Less than 2 files: confirm error message is printed
- Unreadable file: confirm perror is called and program continues
- Three or more files: confirm output is sorted by combined word count descending
- Run valgrind to check for memory leaks

Design Notes:
- Word frequency distributions are stored as singly linked lists sorted in
  lexicographic order. Sorting happens at insert time using strcmp so the
  lists are always ready for the merge walk.
- The JSD merge walk simultaneously iterates both sorted word lists in one
  while loop, handling three cases: word in both files, word only in file 1,
  word only in file 2.
- All comparisons are stored in an array of structs and sorted with qsort
  before printing.
- File I/O uses POSIX open(), read(), and close().
- Words are built dynamically with realloc so there is no maximum word length.